CODE PIPELINE WITH ELASTIC BEANSTALK

1  Create an environment of NODE.JS by using elastic bean stalk.

2  Show them the output by clicking on link

3  Download a basic python code form below link:https://docs.aws.amazon.com/elasticbeanstalk/latest/dg/samples/nodejs.zip

4  Code commit -- > source -- > create Repo -- > select repo and clone url -- > clone HTTPS

5  Open git bash -- >

6  git clone https://git-codecommit.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/v1/repos/swiggy

7  Now it will ask for credentials

8  Create an iam role and adminstartor access

9  Open the user and get http git creds

10  Now it will get repo got to repo inside and check : it will show Mustafa

11  Open your local drive and open that path by selecting any file

12  Now you will find zepto therr

13  Place your node js code on that zepto repo all files

14  Now you will see all of those on git bash use ll command

15  Change application.py and commit those and give git push, the all files will pushed.

16  Pipeline -- > create -- > name -- > next -- > provider: aws code commit -- > repo name : zepto

17  Branch -- > master -- > next -- > skip build stage -- > Deploy provoider : elastic beanstalk

18  Application name -- > environment name -- > next -- > create pipeline

19  Now see the page it will be changed

20  Modify one more time and commit and give git push it will be automatically deployed.
================================================================================================

